---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import NewsletterSignup from '../components/NewsletterSignup.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="synaplex — discovering the structure of AI systems"
  description="A self-learning, self-evolving system for uncovering the structure of AI systems. Publication that builds topology, not timeline. Evaluation lab that emits replayable canon envelopes. Pods that probe the structure from specific domains."
>
  <section class="mb-12">
    <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider mb-3" style="color: var(--color-ink-dim);">
      Discovering the structure of AI systems
    </p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight mb-6">
      AI systems have <span style="color: var(--color-accent);">real structure</span>. We are uncovering it.
    </h1>
    <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed max-w-2xl" style="color: var(--color-ink-dim);">
      synaplex is a self-learning, self-evolving system. It ingests external signal, reasons against its own accumulated canon, validates candidate claims, and publishes what survives. Pods — atlas for systematic crypto, skillfoundry for commercial discovery — are bidirectional probes that uncover invariants and absorb them. The publication isn't a timeline. Each new piece refines the latent shape; old pieces don't age out, they become foundations.
    </p>
  </section>

  <NewsletterSignup />

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 mt-10 tracking-tight">
      How the lab works
    </h2>
    <ol class="space-y-4 max-w-2xl">
      <li>
        <strong>Every evaluation pre-registers its falsification criteria.</strong> The claim is
        recorded in canon before any data is collected. Post-hoc narrative changes don't
        happen here.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Raw artifacts are hash-bound.</strong> Transcripts, datasets, and methodology
        specs are referenced by SHA-256 content hash. Post-hoc edits produce new records,
        not silent overwrites.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Adversarial review before publish.</strong> Every evaluation's methodology is
        pressure-tested against an opposing-perspective agent before the writeup ships.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Sponsored evaluations are cryptographically distinguished.</strong> Paid evals
        carry a <code>Policy.provenance.sponsor</code> attestation in canon. You can always
        tell.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 mt-10 tracking-tight">
      What we're working on
    </h2>
    <ul class="space-y-3 max-w-2xl">
      <li>
        <strong>First lab:</strong> Memory systems comparison — Letta, mem0, MemGPT,
        Claude built-in memory, evaluated on 5 task suites (with one held-out) at
        N≥10 runs per cell. Pre-registration live;
        <a href="/lab/memory-systems-v1/">methodology here</a>.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Intake pipeline:</strong> daily ingestion across RSS, arxiv, HN
        (with Reddit, GitHub, Substack, and podcasts queued); per-beat scoring;
        weekly synthesis. The system's sense organs.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Directory build-out:</strong> harness · memory · orchestration · integration.
        Quality-graded, grown from the lab's evaluation corpus.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Layout>
